# Chat UI and client state

Read `docs/architecture.md` (Message merge, Session identity) before non-trivial changes.

## Components

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `chat-panel.tsx` | Bootstrap session, voice toggle, `TextChatArea`, `useChat`, `useSession`, merge |
| `message-list.tsx` | Renders `ChatMessage[]` |
| `message-input.tsx` | Text send callback |

## Session bootstrap

- `ChatPanel` POSTs `/api/session` when Zustand has no `sessionId`
- `TextChatArea` mounts only when `sessionId` exists, with `key={sessionId}`
- **Why:** `useChat` + `DefaultChatTransport` bind `sessionId` at creation time

## Text chat (`useChat`)

```tsx
new DefaultChatTransport({ api: "/api/chat", body: { sessionId } })
```

- Map AI SDK `UIMessage` → `ChatMessage` with `source: "text"`
- Loading state from `status === "submitted" | "streaming"`

## Zustand store (`chat-store.ts`)

- Persist key: `personal-agent-chat`
- Fields: `sessionId`, `messages`, `voiceMessageIds` (dedup set for voice rows)
- `addVoiceMessage` — idempotent by message id
- Voice messages always have `source: "voice"`

## Merge in `chat-panel.tsx`

```tsx
[...voiceMessages, ...textMessages].sort((a, b) => a.timestamp - b.timestamp)
```

- `voiceMessages`: filtered from store (`source === "voice"`)
- Do not write voice turns from `useSessionMessages` into the store

## Voice toggle handler

- Enable: set new `voiceConnectionId` + `voiceEnabled true` in same toggle
- Disable: `voiceEnabled false` → effect cleanup calls `session.end()`
- On `start()` failure: `onVoiceDisconnect()` resets toggle

## Do not

- Mount/unmount `useSession` when toggling voice (see rule `livekit-voice`)
- Use session transcriptions as persisted chat history
- Create `useChat` before `sessionId` is known
